org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit.files

Class SinglePendingCommit

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit.files.PersistentCommitData
      • org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit.files.SinglePendingCommit
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<String>

    @InterfaceAudience.Private
 @InterfaceStability.Unstable
public class SinglePendingCommit
extends PersistentCommitData
implements Iterable<String>
    This is the serialization format for uploads yet to be committerd. It's marked as Serializable so that it can be passed in RPC calls; for this to work it relies on the fact that java.io ArrayList and LinkedList are serializable. If any other list type is used for etags, it must also be serialized. Jackson expects lists, and it is used to persist to disk.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
